        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I was testing the security of my site with a scanner and it reported the error \"Possible Backup File was found, \" that's not what really happens, but Zend reports an error when it is passed in the url of the parameters below:\r\n\r\n-controllername (http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/-index)\r\ncontrollername- (http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/about-)\r\n~controllername\r\ncontrollername. (http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/download.)\r\n.controllername\r\n_controllername\r\ncontrollername_\r\n\r\nThe error generated is this: script '-controllername\/index.phtml' not found in path \r\n\r\nThe expected would be an \"error 404\" but not what happens.\r\nHow do we arrange this?\r\n\r\n\r\n"
        },
